Members of Elite Itsekiri Social Club, Alpha May Club, Lagos branch have described the demise of Nigeria civil war hero Col Paul Ogbebor, (retd) as a great loss to the country. They stated this when the groups paid a condolence visit to the widow of the deceased, Chief Rita Lori-Ogbebor on Wednesday in Lagos. The delegation led by Mr. Ajijala Rone-Orugbo comprised of Chief J.J Akpieyi-Otuedon, Mr.Tshola Aragho, Mr. Robinson Eyeoyibo, Mr. Lawrence Anirejuoriste Wilbert, and Mr. Henry Hector Amiwero commiserated with Lori-Ogbebor, describing the deceased as an illustrious Nigerian. According Rone-Orugbo, ‘’ Colonel Paul Ogbebor served the country meritoriously and was very patriotic. He was very detribalised and believed in one indivisible Nigeria. His death is a big loss to the country.’’ Also speaking, the widow Chief Rita Lori-Ogbebor described the deceased as a good man, saying he lived a good life. “He lived a fulfilled and wonderful life. I am glad I married a good man,” she said. However, the statement announcing the death of the late civil war hero, reads: “He attended Government Primary School, Benin and Saint Patrick’s College Asaba, Delta State. “Col. Paul was a pioneer cadet of the Nigerian Defence Academy (NDA) and was commissioned in 1967 as a combatant regular officer. “He attended Army Signal School, Fort Monmouth, New jersey, USA, Executive Management programme, Penn State University Pennsylvania, USA (1991).” 